div.p:
Doct XXXIII. is this, That there shall be nothing spoken of, that has been good that evil men have done; but what evil hath been found in them, that shall be mentioned against them in the Day of Judgement. They have done some things that have been good for the matter; as it may be they have Prayed, Fasted, given Alms, and done sundry other things that have bin materially good: but nothing shall be spoken then of what they have so done; 
   •
o mention shall be made of any of them, but onely of their sins.
